The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) has announced the constitution of four committees for the period 2022-26. The committees are, Referees, Match Commissioners, Disciplinary and Appeals. Respected former FIFA referee, Faith Irabor will head the Referees Committee, while Rabiu Umar will serve as vice- president. The Match Commissioners Committee is headed by NFF board, Babangana Alkali, with another member of the football house, Ganiyu Majekodunmi serving as vice-president. Former vice-chairman of the Anambra State Football Association, Barrister JBC Obikwelu will run the affairs of the Disciplinary Committee. The Referees and Match Commissionersâ€™ committees are scheduled to meet with the NFF on Thursday in Abuja in preparation for the 2022/23 season.